How do conservatards always pick literally the worst things  to defend bro. Like is it really that hard just sticking to like a vague racism and shitting on libs and then getting paid for it. Like something just compels them to get out of the party RW line and start experimenting

It just comes down to not wanting to live like an animal. Upholding yourself and others to standards. Valuing purity instead of compromise. This and many other phenomena of this century just show that in spite of heavy superficial setbacks mankind is still actually progressing.

In The Office TV show the Dwight character mentioned that it was a family Schrute tradition for them to marry while standing inside their own future coffins. Like the bridge and groom stand in two coffins and the priest is next to them. I find it very charming as a concept.

I'm just a private eye down on my luck.. taking a walk through the bad part of town, keeping my ears open trying to scoop some rumors from the criminal world.. I sit at a downtown bar order a drink and pretend to read a newspaper, listening in on the regular crooks' conversations

Sitting up late in my office, table lamp on, looking through some old unsolved case files.. Can't sleep. A strange woman walks in and asks me if I've heard about the Chinatown murders from last summer.. I have the bad feeling this affair will turn out to be more sour than sweet..

You know how some people get a "DO NOT RESUSCITATE" tattoo on their chests? I would like to get like the exact polar opposite of that. Maybe like a "DON'T GIVE UP, DOC!" or "TRY THE DEFIBRILLATOR AGAIN". Maybe like a small motivational collage with my doctor's face in the middle.

The "DNR" one is like getting a "Kick me" sticky note tattooed on your back and then walking shirtless. Just a bad way to go about life. Sucker mindset. Like if SS blood group tattoos said "meh, exsanguination sounds pretty ok". That would make them pointless in the first place.

Swimming out far into the sea and telling my friends to yell for help, she swims in to save me, but there's a camouflaged Zhukov type underwater bridge installed as a table, with a bottle of wine and two glasses. Russian military surplus. "PMC Wagner connections" I confess to her
Actually tearing up at the second part
Once again people seem to snipe out the few good aspects of life today with an astonishing precision

Going to a black girl and saying: "NASA said they plan to put a black woman on the moon, but I want to have you all over the moon". Actually I think that's a British expression only. Not as sexual as it sounds at first glance. But they do not have a space program there. No Nazis.

Feels like there should be a bigger market for famous people's toilet seats. Like what happened with Hitler's toilet after the war. I'd be willing to pay some big money to have it shipped to and installed in my house. It's probably a low key billionaire collection type thing.

One time I actually spent an entire microbiology class hiding behind a large Soviet-looking microscope. The professor kept asking everyone individualized questions and I was in the back behind a microscope like a Japanese holdout hiding in Pacific island bushes. She didn't see me

The other students also possessed microscopes but for some reason did not attempt to use them to shield themselves from the professor's field of vision. It was like a school shooting but an inside job and technically non-violent. I cowered, felt like Noah inside the Ark's safety.

I can't really lean into the whole scientific IQ racism shtick because I'm so bad at math that other people always have to calculate my part of restaurant/cafe bills, how much change I have to give them back, etc. We should just stick with the more vague Hyperborea type stuff imo

You know who didn't get IQ tested? Otto Skorzeny. They couldn't catch him in time. By the time he voluntarily surrendered after he was done hiding his collection of stolen art or whatever they had already finished with the IQ tests. And he's overall a pretty smart guy in my book.
